---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../site.config';

const rc = SITE.projects[1];
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Remote Control" theme="rc">
  <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-6 py-10 relative z-10">
    <h1 class="text-[2rem] font-bold text-[var(--color-accent)] mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-500 mb-8 pb-4 border-b border-[#2e2e3a]">
      <strong class="text-slate-300">Remote Control</strong> - Arduino Wake on LAN via MQTT<br />
      Last Updated: July 12, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="bg-[#202027] border border-[#2e2e3a] rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-[var(--color-accent)] text-xl font-semibold mt-0 mb-3">🔒 TL;DR</h2>
      <p class="mb-2 text-slate-300">
        <strong>This project collects no data whatsoever. It runs entirely on your own hardware.</strong>
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-0">
        The Arduino firmware and all related code run locally on your network. Your MQTT broker
        credentials and network details never leave your own infrastructure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-slate-100 text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <div class="bg-emerald-950/40 border border-emerald-500/40 rounded-lg px-4 py-3 mb-4">
      <strong class="text-emerald-400">We collect absolutely NO information.</strong>
    </div>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The Remote Control project does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information. All
      code runs on hardware you own and control.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-slate-100 text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">2. How the Project Works</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">All components operate within your own infrastructure:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong class="text-slate-300">Arduino Firmware</strong>: Runs locally on your Arduino
        device. Connects to the MQTT broker you configure and listens for wake commands.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-slate-300">MQTT Broker</strong>: You choose and configure your own
        broker (e.g., CloudMQTT, Mosquitto). Credentials are stored only in your Arduino sketch and
        your MQTT client.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-slate-300">Wake on LAN</strong>: Magic packets are sent over your local
        network only. No external server is involved in the wake process.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-slate-100 text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">3. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      This project is designed to work with a third-party MQTT broker of your choosing. The privacy
      policy of that broker applies to any data it handles. The project author has no affiliation
      with or access to any broker you use.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-slate-100 text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">4. Data Storage</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      No data is stored by this project. Your MQTT credentials and target MAC addresses live only
      in your Arduino sketch and your MQTT client configuration, both of which you control
      entirely.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-slate-100 text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">5. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Since no data is collected, there is nothing to share. The project author does not receive,
      store, or process any information from users of this project.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-slate-100 text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">6. Open Source</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      This project is fully open source. You can audit every line of code on{' '}
      <a
        href={rc.repoUrl}
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline">GitHub</a
      > to verify these claims independently.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-slate-100 text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Any updates to this policy will be reflected on this page with a revised date. Significant
      changes will also be noted in the repository changelog.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-slate-100 text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">8. Contact</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      For questions or concerns, please open an issue on the{' '}
      <a
        href={rc.repoUrl}
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline">GitHub repository</a
      >.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-[#2e2e3a] text-center text-slate-500">
      <p>{SITE.author.copyright}</p>
      <p class="mt-2">
        <a href="/remote-control/terms" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline"
          >Terms of Use</a
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
